ection demonstrates a set of relations between civilization and ruination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aViolence. 0aX-rays. 4aBody. 4aColonially. 4aCultural Studies. 4aGender. 4aImage. 4aPhotography. 4aRace. 4aRacism. 4aTechnologies. 4aViolence. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aBody.  aColonially.  aCultural Studies.  aGender.  aImage.  aPhotography.  aRace.  aRacism.  aTechnologies.  aViolence.1 aAbbasi Tavallali, Javad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFavero, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHillström, Ella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHussaini, Reza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhosravi Noori, Behzad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhosravi, Shahram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhosravi, Shahram, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrämer, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoeth, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQasmiyeh, Yousif M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSengupta, Partha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharif, Yara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTanimowo Okunseinde, Ayodamola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVergès, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhalley, Joanne ‘Bob’, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package